A Scottish student was left critically injured following an
encounter with a black rhino, in Northern Zululand, KwaZulu-Natal, on
Wednesday. IPSS Medical Rescue said they were contacted and informed
that the game ranger student had been on foot in a private reserve when he was
trampled and gored by the rhino. IPSS said the incident happened on Wednesday morning and
prompted a search and rescue operation by IPSS Search and Rescue as well as
anti-poaching units in the area. The student was located and preparations for evacuation were
initiated, said IPSS The student was critically injured and was taken to
hospital.